channel.title: 2 questions in 1
channel.description:
I'm using EmpireScape source [317] and I wanna change the teleports coordinates, for example if i click the varrock tele it brings me to some stores, what if i wanted to change where it brings me. And how do i make the "Home Teleport" in the spellbook bring me to home?
My second question is, I wanna change some npc coords. For example i wanna change were shops is.

item.title: 2 questions in 1
item.dc:creator: @daxter852 daxter852
item.description:
@daxter852 wrote:

[quote=“xweetok599, post:19, topic:330375”][quote author=daxter852 link=topic=426757.msg3134243#msg3134243 date=1266777449]

1st question: clickingmost.java
2nd question: autospawn.cfg

In the EmpireScape source on one of the teleports it says: Barrows, Fight Pits, Pest Ctrl, D Anarchy and Soon… How do i make the soon tele you somewere? And also How do i make the “Home Teleport” bring you somewere?

EDIT: How does autospawn.cfg work though?
For example what does all this mean?

spawn = 90	3105	3542	0	3106	3543	3104	3541	1

[/quote]
How autospawn works? I think youre a newbie then lol.
The 90 at the code is the NPC ID. 3105 Is the X coord 3542 Y coord 0, IDK, but always let it 0. 3106 is where it can walk in coord X 3543 same but coord Y and the other codes are same too. 3104 is coord X where it can walk, 3541 is coord Y where it can walk. The 1 is that it can walk. If you put that to 0, the NPC can’t walk.[/quote]
I figured that out.
To: Hypocryte
I posted my clickingmost.java here: http://www.runelocus.com/forums/showthread.php?p=503708#post503708
